{
  "local_port": 52830,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I use my laptop effectively?",
  "response": "Using your laptop effectively involves optimizing both hardware and software aspects, as well as adopting good habits to enhance productivity and maintain the device's longevity. Here are practical tips to help you make the most of your laptop:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Organize Your Workspace**\n- **Declutter the Desktop**: Keep your desktop clean and organized. Use folders to group similar files.\n- **External Peripherals**: Use a mouse, external keyboard, or monitor for better ergonomics and productivity.\n- **Proper Lighting**: Ensure your workspace has adequate lighting to reduce eye strain.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Optimize System Performance**\n- **Regular Updates**: Keep your operating system, drivers, and software up to date for security and performance improvements.\n- **Manage Startup Programs**: Disable unnecessary startup programs to speed up boot time (use Task Manager on Windows or System Preferences on macOS).\n- **Clean Up Storage**: Regularly delete unused files, clear cache, and uninstall unnecessary programs. Use tools like CC# Create a disk from a snapshot\n\nTo create a disk, you need the `editor` role or higher. Downloading snapshots is allowed to users with the `viewer` role or higher. For more information, see [Managing access to resources](../../../../iam/operations/resources/manage-resource-access.md).\n\n{% note alert %}\n\nThe disk you're creating should be the same size or larger than the snapshot. If your disk is smaller than the snapshot, your new disk will not work properly. For more information, see [Snapshots](../../concepts/snapshot.md).\n\n{% endnote %}\n\n- To create a disk, use the button ![image](../../../../_assets/plus-sign.svg) **Create disk** on the **Disks** page:\n\n   1. In the [management console]({{ link-console-main }}), select the folder where you want to create a disk.\n   1. Select **{{ compute-name }}**.\n   1. On the left-hand panel, select ![image](../../../../_assets/compute/disks-pic.svg) **Disks**.\n   1. Click **Create disk**.\n   1. Enter the disk name.\n\n      {% include [Disk name requirements](../../../../_includes/compute/name-requirements.md) %}\n\n   1. If required, add a description of the disk.\n   1. Select the [availability zone](../../../../overview/concepts/geo-scope.md) to place the disk in.\n   1. Select the [disk type](../disk.md#disks_types).\n   1. Specify the required disk size.\n   1. Under **Snapshot**, select a snapshot to create the disk from.\n   1. Click **Create disk**.\n\n- To create a disk from a snapshot, use the button ![image](../../../../_assets/context-menu.svg) **Create disk** on the **Snapshots** page.\n\n   1. In the [management console]({{ link-console-main }}), select the folder where you want to create a disk.\n   1. Select **{{ compute-name }}**.\n   1. On the left-hand panel, select ![image](../../../../_assets/compute/snapshots.svg) **Snapshots**.\n   1. Find the required snapshot in the list and click ![image](../../../../_assets/horizontal-ellipsis.svg).\n   1. In the menu that opens, click **In a new disk**.\n   1. Enter the disk name.\n\n      {% include [Disk name requirements](../../../../_includes/compute/name-requirements.md) %}\n\n   1. If required, add a description of the disk.\n   1. Select the [availability zone](../../../../overview/concepts/geo-scope.md) to place the disk in.\n   1. Select the [disk type](../disk.md#disks_types).\n   1. Specify the required disk size.\n   1. Click **Create disk**.\n\nCreate a disk by calling the [create](../../api-ref/Disk/create.md) method for the `Disk` resource:\n\n1. Get the ID of the required snapshot (see the [previous section](delete.md)).\n1. Create the disk:\n\n   {% list tabs %}\n\n   - Bash\n\n     ```bash\n     curl -H \"Authorization: Bearer `yc iam create-token`\" \\\n       -d '{\n         \"folderId\": \"<folder ID>\",\n         \"zoneId\": \"<availability zone>\",\n         \"name\": \"<disk name>\",\n         \"description\": \"<disk description>\",\n         \"typeId\": \"<disk type>\",\n         \"size\": \"<disk size>\",\n         \"sourceSnapshotId\": \"<snapshot ID>\"\n       }' \\\n       -X POST \\\n       https://compute.{{ api-host }}/compute/v1/disks\n     ```\n\n   {% endlist %}\n\n   Where:\n   - `folderId`: [Folder](../../../resource-manager/concepts/resources-hierarchy.md#folder) ID.\n   - `zoneId`: Availability zone.\n   - `name`: Disk name. The name format is as follows:\n\n     {% include [name-format](../../../../_includes/name-format.md) %}\n\n   - `description`: Disk description.\n   - `typeId`: Disk type.\n   - `size`: Disk size.\n   - `sourceSnapshotId`: [Snapshot](index.md#snapshots) ID.\n\n   The disk size should be greater than or equal to the size of the snapshot. The maximum disk size is 4096 GB.\n\n   As a result, the disk created from the snapshot will be available in the folder specified in the `folderId` parameter.\n",
  "temperature": 1.0,
